1. Chsh -s (path of the shell)———> used to change the shell 
2. Echo $0 —————————————>to find the shell we are using 
3. Cat /etc/shells/——————————> to find the path of the shells 
chmod -R (permission you want to give )(folder name )---------> with this formate it will change the permissions for entire files inside the folder 
chown -R (to which user you want to change to ) (folder name)